# Regulatory Export Endpoint Specification

## Endpoint Design

### **Endpoint**
```
GET /exports/regulatory/{reportType}
```

### **Authentication**
- Requires JWT with `StateAuditor` or `FederalAuditor` role
- API key for automated system access

### **Parameters**

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description | Example |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|---------|
| `reportType` | string | Yes | Type of regulatory report | `state-compliance`, `federal-inventory`, `epa-ghgrp` |
| `period` | string | Yes | Reporting period in YYYY-QQ format | `2024-Q1` |
| `facilityId` | string | No | Filter by specific facility (auditor-only) | `f1e2d3c4-b5a6-7890-g1h2-i3j4k5l6m7n8` |
| `includeDetails` | boolean | No | Include detailed line items (default: false) | `true` |
| `format` | string | No | Output format (default: json) | `csv`, `xml` |

### **Response Headers**
```
Content-Type: application/json | text/csv | application/xml
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="emissions_report_{reportType}_{period}.{format}"
Cache-Control: no-store
```

## Data Transformation Rules

### 1. **Deficit Collapsing Logic**
All rebalanced deficits are aggregated into a single municipal variance category according to these rules:

```typescript
interface MunicipalVarianceCategory {
  categoryId: "MUNI-VAR-001";
  categoryName: "Municipal Compliance Variance";
  description: "Aggregated emissions variance absorbed by municipal environmental programs";
  totalQuantity: number; // Sum of all rebalanced deficits
  totalCost: number; // Sum of all public works allocations
  programBreakdown: {
    urbanForestry: number;
    renewableEnergy: number;
    wasteManagement: number;
    other: number;
  };
  notes: "Includes aggregated variances from facility remediation shortfalls per municipal ordinance 2023-12";
}
```

### 2. **Data Transformation Pipeline**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Raw Data] --> B{Has Rebalanced Deficits?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Aggregate Deficits]
    C --> D[Create Municipal Variance Category]
    B -->|No| E[Proceed Normally]
    D --> F[Merge with Facility Data]
    E --> F
    F --> G{Report Type?}
    G -->|State| H[Apply State Formatting]
    G -->|Federal| I[Apply Federal Formatting]
    G -->|EPA GHGRP| J[Apply EPA Formatting]
    H --> K[Final Export]
    I --> K
    J --> K
```

